    <item>
      <title>Please develop an old-school (EQ + Kunark only) IRON MAN PVP Server</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Progression&amp;message.id=12494#M12494</link>
      <description>&lt;div&gt;I really believe that EQ as a game would benefit from having a PVP &amp;quot;Iron Man&amp;quot; server on which any death taken (either through PVP or through PVE play) would result in a return to lvl 1 and the loss of all items and cash.  It should only be possible to have one character at a time on this sever to level the playing field for all. &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Sony hosted a great &amp;quot;Iron Man&amp;quot; event for one month over the Christmas holiday season a few years ago, and that event was the BEST time I've ever had playing EQ or any online RPG.  Just imagine the excitement of facing evil monsters in unknown zones if you have your entire character LIFE on the line?  How brave and daring would characters on this IRON MAN sever be?  And..to top it all off..add to that PVE excitement the excitement of PVP!  Just knowing that your entire character life is not really &amp;quot;safe&amp;quot; anywhere in Norath would add a level of excitement to the game that I really feel has been lacking ever since Sony teased us with that IRON Man contest a few years ago!  :) &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Please, please, please look into adding a permanent IRON MAN PVP server with only Everquest Classic plus the Kunark expansion -- back when PVP was at its peak and there was no &amp;quot;booking&amp;quot; to avoid certain death. &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt; &lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;Permanent character death (Iron Man) servers are a rarity on all of the online RPGs at the moment, and I believe SONY would win big points and expand its customer base if they were to consider instituting an Iron Man PvP server! &lt;/div&gt;</description>
